            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a Belgian man, his daughter, and his mother with brain small vessel disease-1 (BSVD1; 175780), Lemmens et al. (2013) identified a heterozygous 1-bp deletion (c.2085delC) in the COL4A1 gene, resulting in a frameshift and premature termination (Gly696fs). The mutation was not found in the 1000 Genomes Project, dbSNP (build 135), and Exome Variant Server databases, or in 744 control individuals. Patient cells showed no mutant COL4A1 mRNA, suggesting nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. Western blot analysis of patient cells showed a 41% reduction in COL4A1 expression; these findings were consistent with haploinsufficiency.</Attribute>
              <Citation>
                <CitationText>Lemmens, R. Personal Communication. 2014. Leuven, Belgium</CitationText>
